# UI Components (`components/`)

## Folder Structure
| Folder | Domain | Components |
|--------|--------|------------|
| `components/ui/` | Generic primitives (no domain knowledge) | `back-button`, `submit-button`, `icons` |
| `components/access/` | Access code gate (landing page) | `access-code-gate` |
| `components/celulas/` | Cell domain | `celula-context`, `celula-selector`, `celula-list`, `celula-form` |
| `components/setores/` | Sector domain | `setor-context` |
| `components/membros/` | Member domain | `member-form`, `member-personal-fields`, `member-trajectory-fields`, `member-trajectory-sheet`, `member-list`, `member-self-register-share` |
| `components/trajetoria/` | Trajectory accordion sections | `trajetoria-section` |
| `components/insights/` | Analytics / insights panel | `insights-panel` |
| `components/behavior/` | Infrastructure / lifecycle | `leader-page-refresh` |

## Client-Only Imports
These components are `"use client"`. They may import from:
- `lib/trajetoria.ts` — trajectory steps, categories, totals, `computeTrajectoryInsights`
- `lib/constants.ts` — `MEMBER_FORM_FIELDS`, `CELULA_FORM_FIELDS`
- `lib/types.ts` — `CelulaOption`, `UnidadeOption`, `MemberListItem`, `MemberFormValues`, `SaveMemberState`, `SaveCelulaState`, `TrajectoryInsights`, etc.
- `lib/routes.ts` — URL builders
- `lib/formatting.ts` — `formatPhone`, `formatBirthDate`, `formatCreatedAt`

Never import from `lib/celulas/`, `lib/membros/`, `lib/unidades/`, `lib/rotas.ts`, `lib/form-helpers.ts`, or `lib/supabase/*`.

## Member Form Contract
- `MemberForm` uses `useActionState` with a server action passed as prop.
- All form `name` attributes use `MEMBER_FORM_FIELDS` constants.
- Trajectory selections are React-controlled state. Selected values are submitted via hidden `<input>` elements with `name={MEMBER_FORM_FIELDS.passosConcluidos}` — one per selected step. Server reads them with `formData.getAll(...)`.
- `codigo_acesso` and `celula_id` are also submitted as hidden inputs.
- Do not convert this to uncontrolled checkboxes without also updating `getSelectedPassos` in `lib/membros/validation.ts`.

## Cell Form Contract
- `CelulaForm` uses `useActionState` with `saveSetorCelulaAction`.
- All form `name` attributes use `CELULA_FORM_FIELDS` constants.
- `unidade_codigo_acesso` is submitted as a hidden input.

## Insights Panel
- `InsightsPanel` is a reusable client component that accepts `members` and optional `celulas`/`totalCelulas` props.
- It uses `computeTrajectoryInsights` from `trajetoria.ts` — never inline trajectory math.
- When `celulas` prop is provided (setor context), it renders a per-cell trajectory ranking section.
- When `celulas` is not provided (celula context), only general insights are shown.

## Component Structure
- `MemberForm` composes: `CelulaSelector` (from `celulas/`), `MemberPersonalFields`, `MemberTrajectoryFields`, `SubmitButton` (from `ui/`).
- `MemberList` composes: `MemberSelfRegisterShare`, `InsightsPanel` (from `insights/`), `MemberTrajectorySheet`.
- `CelulaList` renders cell cards with links to `/lider/[codigo]` and a "Cadastrar celula" button.
- `InsightsPanel` renders: `StatCard` grid, category `ProgressBar` list, and optional `CelulaRankingList`.
- Keep each subcomponent focused on its section. Shared state (form values, errors) is passed as props.

## Key Components
| Component | Location | Purpose |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| `member-list.tsx` | `membros/` | Member listing with trajectory progress bars and insights |
| `celula-list.tsx` | `celulas/` | Cell listing for sector view with "Cadastrar celula" button |
| `celula-form.tsx` | `celulas/` | Cell creation form (nome, lideres, dia_semana, horario, codigo_acesso) |
| `insights-panel.tsx` | `insights/` | Trajectory insights with stat cards, category progress, and per-cell ranking |
| `setor-context.tsx` | `setores/` | Unit (setor/rede/sede) context card for header |
| `celula-context.tsx` | `celulas/` | Cell context card (`CelulaContextCard`, `CelulaAvatar`) |
| `back-button.tsx` | `ui/` | History-based back navigation in headers |
| `access-code-gate.tsx` | `access/` | Unified access code form with celula/setor toggle |
| `icons.tsx` | `ui/` | Shared icon wrappers (leader, schedule, accordion, pastoreio, save, etc.) |

## Mobile-First & Accessibility
- Touch targets: minimum 44x44px.
- Use accessible contrast ratios.
- Prefer large, clear labels over icon-only controls.
- Test visual hierarchy on narrow viewports first.
